text: Washington County is a county located in the U.S. state of North Carolina. As of the 2020 Census, the population was 11,003. Its county seat is Plymouth. The county was formed in 1799 from the western third of Tyrrell County. It was named for George Washington, the first President of the United States. == References == Category:1790s establishments in North Carolina Category:1799 establishments in the United States Category:North Carolina counties
title: Washington County, North Carolina
